==Awards and nominations==
In 2010, Hart won the Best Comedy Performance award from the [[Royal Television Society]] for her performance in ''Miranda''<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/7460124/Royal-Television-Society-Awards-shun-talent-shows.html |title=Royal Television Society Awards shun talent shows |newspaper=Daily Telegraph |date=17 March 2010 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100529043236/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/7460124/Royal-Television-Society-Awards-shun-talent-shows.html |archivedate=29 May 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and was also nominated for best comedy writing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inthenews.co.uk/news/entertainment/tv/miranda-heads-royal-television-society-awards-nominations-$1363108.htm |title=Miranda heads Royal Television Society awards nominations |website=Inthenews.co.uk |first=Lewis |last=Bazley |date=1 March 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224122705/http://www.inthenews.co.uk/news/entertainment/tv/miranda-heads-royal-television-society-awards-nominations-$1363108.htm |archivedate=24 December 2013}}</ref> She and [[Patricia Hodge]] were both nominated for "Best Comedy Actress" awards at the Monte-Carlo TV Festival 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvfestival.com/content/Presentation-Nominees/presentation_nomineesUK.php?menu=smenu2&trk=nom&typeN=2&ER=TC |title=Nominees – Actresses |website=Monte-Carlo TV Festival |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717115420/http://www.tvfestival.com/content/Presentation-Nominees/presentation_nomineesUK.php?menu=smenu2&trk=nom&typeN=2&ER=TC |archivedate=17 July 2011}}</ref>

In 2011, she won<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a299572/in-full-british-comedy-awards-winners.html |title=British Comedy Awards Winners |website=DigitalSpy |date=22 January 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401031322/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a299572/in-full-british-comedy-awards-winners.html |archivedate=1 April 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> "Best Comedy Actress" and "People's Choice Award for the King or Queen of Comedy" in the [[British Comedy Awards]] 2011, where ''Miranda'' also won "Best New British TV Comedy" and was nominated for "Best Sitcom".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a298153/british-comedy-awards-the-nominations.html |title=British Comedy Awards Nominations |website=DigitalSpy |date=15 January 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110119014856/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a298153/british-comedy-awards-the-nominations.html |archivedate=19 January 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The same year, she was nominated for a [[BAFTA]] for Best Actress in a comedy role and her hit BBC Two sitcom ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]'' was nominated for the BAFTA YouTube choice award, the only award voted for by the public.

